cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on software firms participating in OSS projects and proposes a conceptual model to explain coopetition among them.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of conflicting values among firms on the common goal of OSS projects.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper explores collaboration among firms across organizational boundaries in OSS projects.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper may touch upon technical aspects of OSS projects and software development.
